    summary: "The `swiggy-mcp-server-manifest` refers to a public GitHub repository maintained by Swiggy[1][2]. This repository contains the manifest files for Swiggy\'s Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers[3][4][2][5].\n\nThe Model Context Protocol (MCP) is a permission-based protocol designed to allow AI models and various client applications to interact with Swiggy\'s services in a structured and secure way[5]. This enables functionalities such as AI models understanding natural language to search for restaurants, browse menus, manage shopping carts, and place orders through Swiggy Food, Instamart, and Dineout platforms[6][3][4][2][5].\n\nSeveral tools and platforms utilize these MCP servers, including the community-built `swiggy-cli` command-line interface[3], LobeHub[6], and AI assistants like Claude Desktop, VS Code Copilot, and Cursor[4][2][5].\n\nImportant considerations when using these MCP integrations include current limitations on third-party app development, the recommendation to avoid using the Swiggy mobile app concurrently to prevent session conflicts, and a caution regarding Cash On Delivery (COD) orders, which are currently irreversible once placed[2]. The protocol ensures that AI models only access predefined tools and do not directly interact with Swiggy\'s internal databases or payment systems[5].\n\nSources:\n[1] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG2rICiPJzkasuOX9wvTUsB8h_anj5jviaAZmOt1fmeF5gUy1ebmBxPatqhvO4mLgy1y81v-HnewaPvC9_bsQISZVf3q10atUyC8x4nfVpw_nW_q5Q=)\n[2] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEkc8WtX9s1XR9TgXFue0fFoYDPl1x_hS2UF7SXYUvlDZ9Q7OdfSNWCc98UUC7egmVBzuLh5d2Y8KNXJNiDRqFq1iMyQ5eNOiWvoJwKBJgeEpf_6ZnZz2D6t3UsuZFuAbsf2hAbH_rvx5pvk5eH7iE=)\n[3] [jsdelivr.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFuxOSoJt47NN30P1KyHhd5hen8f7oIpzUXVcx6z_9SXHEZ2VTczZjY4jgHiauoycaKtRWX_KbsDYrGDrgekR1EGMyTDhIeYT179E0ki3MNVYfNS7FWJio