      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHRNvlvGbTF3-vXt3RzAxQwNx5PpKa9pBIWcni8VcwG6Meqfcn64UMaGQ-SZaj2iB_dzgp4HRBCY7BtinJxTp7qq1zaiwmg6rRjziBIknbrfl-HO4PxCijJ5oNnq-rhTHOOAKav3Mk="
      title: "youtube.com"
    }
    summary: "Swiggy\'s MCP (Model Context Protocol) Server is a framework that facilitates intelligent integrations, allowing AI assistants to interact directly with Swiggy\'s services for ordering food, groceries, and more[1][2][3]. The GitHub repository `Swiggy/swiggy-mcp-server-manifest` provides details on the server\'s capabilities and its integration with external platforms[1].\n\nKey aspects of the Swiggy MCP Server include:\n*   **Purpose** The MCP Server acts as a bridge, enabling AI models to securely access live services such as menus, product catalogs, prices, and delivery slots, and to perform actions within the Swiggy platform with user permission[2]. This means users can order food or groceries using natural language commands through AI assistants like ChatGPT and Gemini[3][4].\n*   **Supported Features** The integrations support functionalities like restaurant search, menu browsing, cart management, and seamless food ordering with order tracking[1]. It also extends to Instamart for groceries and Dineout for restaurant bookings[2][3].\n*   **How it Works** When a user makes a request to an AI assistant, the AI converts it into a structured action request that is sent to the Swiggy MCP Server. The server then verifies user authentication, checks what actions the AI is permitted to perform, maintains context (like past orders), and safely calls Swiggy\'s internal APIs to fulfill the request[3][4].\n*   **Integration and Security** MCP is a backend integration layer, not a separate feature within the Swiggy app[3]. It is a permission-based protocol that ensures AI models only call predefined tools and never directly access internal databases or payment information, thus maintaining security and validation within Swiggy\'s backend[4].\n*   **Limitations** Currently, third-party app development is not permitted due to ongoing security reviews. Users are also cautioned against opening the Swiggy app simultaneously with MCP integrations to avoid session conflicts or order processing issues. Additionally, users should be careful with Cash on Delivery (COD) orders as orders placed cannot be canceled[1].\n*   **Access Points** The GitHub manifest lists the connection endpoints for various Swiggy services, including `https://mcp.swiggy.com/food`, `https://mcp.swiggy.com/im` (Instamart), and `https://mcp.swiggy.com/dineout`[1][2]. It also details supported OAuth Redirect URIs for authentication with platforms like Claude, ChatGPT, and VS Code[1].\n\nSources:\n[1] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHEVKF4tK6wEunV1i4ENancMyBAQyTpBpdWYR0ky1n86FdLMFDkwYn2B1ldROhFYqpW6JcZBzq_m7IFd6RV5WC0aOE4hnpdEekLzZpgpI4iRVAK2nUXxpar7qyK6LMW88T88Ek49t8gDwg69NuWJOI=)\n[2] [ndtv.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH09mY75ghVRBgi-0exhfzp69fsEa3e1e-vQBvrDVapZ70QKdygv29EbhkAf9B4o2ywHQDdGcZ3cFFO2oyRzpSLn1GEJ2NmYdN7cOe5swuBxTVGCeog3OjssAuZwyrB4X6PiJy7EDVTfbaX-W7fw9KNXO4C9Pzd1KF15N4z65gmT07Vz3LVbje7rlj7BmEYGdU7m9eZMXzPpUqdDL4bM22Lks1FliGzGaNw18AW5H9eNlk1BQ==)\n[3] [geeksforgeeks.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE2MjrWtdHZr5mt5-VaZvylp41dE08TkThsHDJhk4g6d15vrS7UYmvD_uWy4Cc-3LMHx-RQBbIutx5Bhp4pcWVkIM0JZe-ASim2nrqLTWUhV9_undFF8LcxAvplF8qy9jyAupjTA3OceA9XCrrkgQ==)\n[4] [youtube.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHRNvlvGbTF3-vXt3RzAxQwNx5PpKa9pBIWcni8VcwG6Meqfcn64UMaGQ-SZaj2iB_dzgp4HRBCY7BtinJxTp7qq1zaiwmg6rRjziBIknbrfl-HO4PxCijJ5oNnq-rhTHOOAKav3Mk=)"
