    }
    summary: "The search query \"site:github.com/Swiggy/swiggy-mcp-server-manifest openapi\" did not directly return results within the specified GitHub repository that explicitly mention \"openapi\" in the context of its manifest or direct files.\n\nHowever, \"OpenAPI\" generally refers to the OpenAPI Specification (OAS), which is a widely used, programming language-agnostic interface description format for HTTP APIs, particularly REST APIs[1][2]. It was previously known as the Swagger Specification[3]. The specification allows both humans and machines to understand the capabilities of a service without needing access to source code or additional documentation[2].\n\nKey aspects of OpenAPI include:\n*   **Purpose:** It provides a formal, machine-readable standard for describing API structure, syntax, available endpoints, operation parameters, and authentication methods[1][4].\n*   **Format:** OpenAPI documents are typically written in YAML or JSON[1][2].\n*   **Benefits:** It facilitates the generation of interactive documentation, client SDKs, server stubs (scaffolding), and test cases, helping to keep documentation and code in sync and reducing manual effort and errors[3][1][4]. It also enables seamless integration across various platforms and services[1].\n*   **Community:** The OpenAPI Specification is a community-driven open specification within the OpenAPI Initiative, a Linux Foundation Collaborative Project[2].\n\nWhile the search didn\'t yield specific files or mentions of \"openapi\" directly within the `Swiggy/swiggy-mcp-server-manifest` repository, it is a common practice for microservices, like those implied by \"mcp-server-manifest,\" to utilize OpenAPI for API definition and documentation.\n\nSources:\n[1] [ibm.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHHoG_O73mJ3-IM24WeNEjPMSFhUNntfL6sBuSqh4UZPZvLIkDzmqziQ7soUs4RD1-PI-_DL4EtWLVy9z0-xspRLa0vzOyBhSV0HF8l_ZKH_Qr8Kaqy_RV6wJPPY6rYYlOBKs3o)\n[2] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFjTli6jOifHqxUWc4VqTLdVPFx8sfTvGsTriFYwwpp07ciEzYVLXu82sKeaiLtois9n6pHodeiQI8sl8Zg97llesAZBFdE5W62zb58e4jn5kDAFkBGhjVZYft_jO6HfLaJNCfz6BrFRQ==)\n[3] [wikipedia.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHMTkz-GDpz2Y9MCfquKWK5jh14kFNtC5U0ttUPcXsXOaq4a0IqPy2GHhuHEF2IE05klYC5DU-K81qqeNlPrlzs7oIMpK3MTTrocQmKYoJFmu3KqqVqn-IbS_UaaJRFFVyoAnKxrpdJ2xak5TdxEQ==)\n[4] [openapis.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEVqfChDg8QIBBn63AAiObzJIDAShS3XYo9EtSGmafbWnptQJ0JGJKRUQhec7PKbm59bTCDKW3BS8l04-hBsH0R4CLq4IsH-WZFJDAKP4K3sSTYz-I=)\n[5] [ibm.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGfIUMenJTdkTevOn9-UrjJfXE1hDFkbfQjaodL8AedQfR6TA0lEiOP2_QtWM_XbRfsZ0Dro54jTtnSHu-4JSr_MIrabvrE1D2EMHd4QkSEblA_Urldw-OuLf_d2Cl6P0iACAgC)\n[6] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHCleR6t2vtFaBgkWzMoWNiVUChLnQlMBLoh26n-ZjKiZDRJpXIk9FeLAX3qTIuios1pGHDiKxIY3rMdF_qPHlxn-LRbWwfhg92qiHDWLNAVa3rASQaMUeBX3NSo2v_pS2Ahc4B7BYZLA==)\n[7] [wikipedia.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHQ8s_DSsB09rKZS_vLTFvqVNywDhTF22pEAy1YjJU2cnpRS7_3f1BjIMUTuIFS-NWn122Iqi0IC3Cua5f2AG50LCqNQcolpTC51GaIPXUECrIN_AEMKC5MIjGnk9NmdXbo_BYrdzfkkuusdTR6FQ==)\n[8] [openapis.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFceCtTy2Ih1Dl-BuUjGoLq_ejfjQKBTGcMKMpM4mJ3iBA4fjTZ-mhHK9Ppq2MM_gep4UuYj1I2sKiSPswrWxdRg2LMA2jhkf4vt9wqMvV5EbzarTw=)"
