      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEDAOohm6dGNlNwq6jjVhZRO34X2pWx6-c4vOPuzQ_W3AIEi7b4nZn09UytWglQb7g53xD31sTfqViG7mpz34W1XcOjdYKR-pFsKo8S-0A-fzA60II3OU5fNrxnRfzcZfmwYBZw5pucKQPw9ktYtOR-ZmHy053Vzxt02n9A0EtST3IfO3Gn3s7h"
      title: "lobehub.com"
    }
    web_documents {
      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFCCgEWid2oWtQfW1nmmcuENx79cB-YBsZKHH3622ryPMhA2r3Zct0vCvRC9XDk_gJgKInMgqqboAy31BdlCb0z3ZwLx0lJOplOCoD3HvNWIGdhNx4hnzE67BFtAlS8rB-1D3iKpg=="
      title: "augmentcode.com"
    }
    summary: "The \"swiggy-mcp-server-manifest\" refers to the overall collection and definition of the Swiggy Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers and the tools they expose for AI agent integration. Instead of a single \"manifest.json\" or \"openapi.yaml\" file providing a comprehensive list of all contents, it points to the functionalities offered by Swiggy\'s three distinct MCP servers: Food, Instamart, and Dineout.[1][2][3][4]\n\nKey aspects of the \"swiggy-mcp-server-manifest\" include:\n*   **Three MCP Servers** Swiggy\'s commerce platform is exposed through three independent MCP servers: Food (for restaurant discovery, menus, ordering, and tracking), Instamart (for quick-commerce groceries), and Dineout (for table reservations).[1][2][3][4]\n*   **Tool Catalog** These three servers collectively expose 35 tools, allowing AI agents to perform various actions like searching for restaurants, adding items to a cart, managing orders, and booking tables.[2][3]\n*   **GitHub Repository** A central reference for the Swiggy MCP servers is the GitHub repository `Swiggy/swiggy-mcp-server-manifest`.[5][6][7] This repository is where Swiggy publishes information related to these MCP servers.[5]\n*   **Client-side Configuration** For client-side setup, such as in platforms like LobeHub, a local `mcp.json` file might be used to manually configure MCP servers, including a reference to `swiggy-swiggy-mcp-server-manifest` within an `mcpServers` object.[8] This configuration typically specifies arguments and commands for connecting to the MCP servers.[8]\n*   **API Definitions** While not a single, directly accessible `openapi.yaml` for the entire manifest, the Model Context Protocol itself allows AI agents to interact with external tools, and there are mechanisms, like `openapi-mcp` servers, that can convert OpenAPI specifications into MCP toolsets.[9] This suggests that underlying API definitions may exist in an OpenAPI format.\n\nSources:\n[1] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFAwBuP06LZPELjuoyrk2F2ZDt6na1DpHeeC0u9KAYW1x1_CLiMEA_YVq8EQ6W-8ye8q3X9bu05nejXJHqXTilAgi1qVGMdCaZFubVC_RYHuA23BhzzPPu1nK1zE5J6opYumqQebnGa0h31WT6caHzmnJk6GEwAcoM=)\n[2] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHS23h240wj80Mq20BSFgbjBzRCKqFGLVxW09GWPpjSvy9qlhWSS9fkiCfTrFsZMwjRvnQBkRoemlEtIvcYv6tUczmFw2aL1aUzL-hQKe8CVH2GkY5yEGZr8vZi4fNOydWuQtTDupUQS0w=)\n[3] [medium.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEzAF5qwh-ASLYdQXhsyE0BFMHuxvOqTBGvW-P0BR0iPooNzdByDpJrtRNEtSaiskP21Ev09dIhmvZrxjRT32d1ywZWcGLHQYtXyU2lPggl-NMpfL4JItBBS4w5Zy4p-RC4WG2WvxvAJ-FgFdFaev4lOSCLC8HTDI9VeCUrIBhztsV1BEf34IZ8xu-znhiuzyFKhpVjsRBNlRpI_D9RZ3wq2uteQID2FGCmTP8FsA78UU5HKIEzDwifL4OZHXAWs1EY2GZUpEw=)\n[4] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHqqivnob4NJEieFZHMZ-mHvbEeSvdzyIs_SBYI2l0eCOmM1KKdN8vrXbIqYdO3B0Y_-GN8ySN9W5EZ_FI_mS8EDFFPYGFqKcW9_Idrt3n2cMPNcpwilLRPochAqYlJmw==)\n[5] [jsdelivr.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFfX9emHNwXLwcNNznAi2-tVBf_hOBUuEXLHdJfVdtz2GtuW8ZCwe2DgpNNLK-V9r6gcy0yRSicVNXuH8hzvcgxdnaBKPEnZcXaq5F26YzN0CyTHBEbyIO3L4frPi5ePFNsfCLV5yzTz4I=)\n[6] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGTQ6uhDwCIPh_aNPdnm24In_3OQpeerd_hbvnixh79rfxN7CmodcCbRpRkB_LOmwGnVqW5GxpFfddxiJxkdaVI_NfCK0A5_a_wKhyI8ZPKMh7ASQ8D7Ce8PeUBYSi17DMChUwm3zAkcfqTsRzEYA==)\n[7] [youtube.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFz52w8aEvUaV0_NbH2GSFNRBk626Y0fRxR--7ec4Hi5IOH1hBeyph6rXV-T2XSSXqp7HlLo6oQkYRLw488yi5f0FPfbT4GZXny_b79j1Pushi33X4fMwOEFegDbEpeU7HM1zJmYA==)\n[8] [lobehub.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEDAOohm6dGNlNwq6jjVhZRO34X2pWx6-c4vOPuzQ_W3AIEi7b4nZn09UytWglQb7g53xD31sTfqViG7mpz34W1XcOjdYKR-pFsKo8S-0A-fzA60II3OU5fNrxnRfzcZfmwYBZw5pucKQPw9ktYtOR-ZmHy053Vzxt02n9A0EtST3IfO3Gn3s7h)\n[9] [aug