    summary: "Swiggy\'s Instamart service utilizes a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server, which is part of a larger MCP stack that also includes Food and Dineout services. These MCP servers expose various API tools for functionalities such as product search, cart management, and order placement[1][2].\n\nWhile direct OpenAPI (Swagger) specifications or comprehensive YAML/JSON schema files for the Instamart MCP server were not explicitly found, the following details are available:\n\n*   **MCP Server Manifest:** The Swiggy/swiggy-mcp-server-manifest GitHub repository is the source where Swiggy publishes its Model Context Protocol servers[3][4][5].\n*   **Live Schema Discovery:** The `swiggy-cli`, an unofficial command-line wrapper for these MCP servers, discovers tools at runtime via an \"MCP tools/list RPC\" and pulls schemas live, rather than relying on hard-coded definitions[3].\n*   **JSON Output:** The `swiggy-cli` supports a stable JSON envelope for its output, providing parseable JSON data when interacting with the MCP servers[3].\n*   **Manual Setup Configuration:** Manual setup instructions for integrating with Swiggy MCP servers (including Instamart) mention updating a `mcp.json` configuration file, indicating that JSON is used for configuration[1].\n*   **API Endpoints:** The Instamart MCP server is accessible via the URL `https://mcp.swiggy.com/im`[1][6][2].\n*   **Builders Club:** Swiggy offers a \"Builders Club\" program that provides live API access to Food, Instamart, and Dineout APIs for building AI agents, apps, and integrations[7].\n\nDevelopers looking to interact with the Swiggy Instamart MCP server can explore the `swiggy-mcp-server-manifest` repository on GitHub and potentially use the `swiggy-cli` for programmatic interaction and schema discovery through its live tool-listing and JSON output capabilities[3][4][5].\n\nSources:\n[1] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEWOTmv1cuVqwii-I0SGXpzTOzXMZsWxOEX6EmZ45KLn4YhoAEkJllRYrTZn0jtoWbAO8rpJMxDjIXIcz2LrfCCWDR3ZRb6U0cwVccwWP23s_tvezKKVbHoX9wDWehptQMFFh80G2rdP98bJ5YdeYo=)\n[2] [medium.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEgFTVX14ws2Y9pPkviC9S11mYkuKbfP7gNnkoaN-kK9YCGMs41WgDLVatVT1pN4_Dwx4CM7-g4lIa_lgFxVR4wpg0P4oc_gbM6MuVjwDH0ojifkDeDIIXFbnQJFwqSYOi4AC5OJvfy_bCJtBhRK3unWk0cgl8GPj_c3WsziG5hjKS4lKEFHLs_FcWWHzaMcFuikcAyhQms8VH_jW7Uq_pcUA35lOcAME0QTYsuWf30QcJyGvMroh1YN2D965CbXOwWfrWJWxd1)\n[3] [jsdelivr.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG-ZHmafI4WhKDBUrYbTyc0lfWKPtQhxLZbvr5Ctox_Gn0sXfD-BKHyMY0DHs9qw61-oOIuRK2bpEprwofBpdWL2OLcnEppUP5c75oepfiZCbBB3lcU8nVcfQUWDXunGkzIag4SjZv-6dKr)\n[4] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQELigwAWaCns4PHTJnE1mjcTdjepPSyOyDJNJWFd9cskLifDCafyTXw4pbiJpJFQ7UrictRZMke03AWqt-GK8R-82q6nuJWLfW-r4igv43kVNP4FbwLncZtZfBI2icZOxdnSjAMo3gF3-1IeCZcyg57QbL-XtZRdV94)\n[5] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGxLYX4-m6SqqGwqLq6WKQp_NW9Q48KJ2sJi0KOTfQ7BThBuPRvIzk_udQ2VE4l5huHrexp-xXDSOrze0gIjhOosmq5td7QhnRuBUgP7YHp_rf99kg=)\n[6] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHtMABub2aem8w3RpyF8JQpu_gJUaQPuNE152FmJXqDJmFXrQpEorZtc6uOzPfhSqaHlTIu5EvThLNONJRhHuE6JH5s47y262EPsGoKQdzl59cJWYPRi2zSzYy5Vx2Ul6AaDq9KGhi5t9LvTA==)\n[7] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFmiCdXZyX_dadfPyROkuOkjFQwqrW3RmCsAPdeSGArzjoo4ixL1eLToct7SPb3N9afDebZZvaDCaxRkcrJ-SVBBl4i2StKqm8pu7xF2RlvNQoqThLeKL62c6F1)"
