      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFDpjBZ7slHBD2FsuaxBejOlNNrfyHub1dKml5Ux9tdGYna2tw3Br0RfyKusvqxrElBTr8whWY9NRcQvmyyKp6mjURmra3bXLcPSbIbHjhbm1gIAeTHll-SvfcOmSZn7WS4Rwldh4roRFyt"
      title: "jsdelivr.com"
    }
    web_documents {
      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEnziMqLa4ntGjLN5Zu1n7DanetkTEKtOAvjonySpBs3-TV5aRzwX5FXjfy02WjD6fyWsmSDhwNnNGK1InhzwfwINSiBq4ndIS7faDIwV1jhO46uSug8WtXVext"
      title: "swiggy.com"
    }
    summary: "The Swiggy Instamart component of the `swiggy-mcp-server-manifest` provides an AI-powered grocery and essentials shopping assistant with a dedicated endpoint and a suite of tools for various functionalities[1].\n\n**Instamart Endpoint:**\nThe primary endpoint for the Swiggy Instamart MCP server is `POST mcp.swiggy.com/im`[1][2][3].\n\n**Instamart Tools and Functionality:**\nThe Instamart MCP server offers 13 tools, categorized into \"Discover,\" \"Cart,\" \"Order,\" and \"Track\" functionalities[1][3]. These tools enable AI agents to perform complex tasks using natural language prompts, bypassing traditional app interfaces[4][5].\n\n*   **Discover:**\n    *   `create_address`: Create a new delivery address for the authenticated user[1].\n    *   `delete_address`: Delete a saved delivery address[1].\n    *   `get_addresses`: Retrieve all saved delivery addresses for the authenticated user[1].\n    *   `search_products`: Search for available products at a selected address, including variants like pack sizes and quantities[1].\n    *   `your_go_to_items`: Fetch frequently or recently ordered items for a selected delivery address[1].\n\n*   **Cart:**\n    *   `clear_cart`: Remove all items from the Instamart cart[1].\n    *   `get_cart`: Get the current Instamart grocery cart with all items and bill breakdown[1].\n    *   `update_cart`: Replace the entire cart with provided items[1].\n\n*   **Order:**\n    *   `checkout`: Place and confirm a Swiggy Instamart grocery order, creating the order and confirming payment in a single operation[1].\n\n*   **Track:**\n    *   `get_order_details`: Get detailed information for a specific Instamart order by ID[1].\n    *   `get_orders`: Fetch Instamart order history[1].\n    *   `track_order`: Track the real-time status of a Swiggy Instamart order[1].\n\n**General Details and Context:**\nThe Swiggy MCP (Model Context Protocol) is an open-source framework that connects AI systems and chatbots to live data, sources, and services, enabling secure interaction with external applications[4][5]. Instamart was the first quick-commerce platform globally to adopt MCP, allowing users to browse and purchase from over 40,000 SKUs using natural language[3][4][5].\n\n**Authentication:**\nAuthentication for the Swiggy MCP servers, including Instamart, relies on standard OAuth 2.1 with PKCE (Proof Key for Code Exchange)[3][6].\n\n**Tools and Ecosystem:**\nAn unofficial, community-built command-line interface (CLI) called `swiggy-cli` is available, which acts as a wrapper around the Swiggy MCP servers (Food, Instamart, Dineout). This CLI provides an ergonomic interface for developers and agents[7]. Swiggy also encourages building AI agents, apps, and integrations on their MCP APIs through the \"Swiggy Builders Club\"[8].\n\n**Limitations and Important Notes:**\n*   Currently, third-party app development is not permitted due to ongoing security reviews and compliance requirements[2].\n*   The Swiggy MCP serves an India-only user base[6].\n*   Production access is invite-based and requires whitelist onboarding[6].\n*   Users should avoid opening the Swiggy app while using MCP integrations to prevent session conflicts or order processing issues[2].\n*   Orders placed through the MCP are currently for Cash On Delivery (COD) only and cannot be canceled, emphasizing the need to review the cart before checkout[2].\n\nSources:\n[1] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH4fdXOSoPJJHiJEpF_SMhZp_ny31TJgw9uPHjrI7LlUm-KFfldlcGqkZN05rcruP59mDUXJp2f5YT9gG1YhaaB2QIfDvwo4yb--2QB6zyMl7-d1GL5qkYYiKrhNmHpknP0PqKOwxq4ym-swlRrN0Uouhsd_g==)\n[2] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEtklAwjWt3dwXRTNvvBTDjel3Y73bn4qqH24f2s5MnfxjCUpvVdFxmlRuZzNN4QBwepPxSaGJTrK2Vw-qTFv10zWmAX9_OnLea31hEddaNFnmm4qSGEnaOjXyum2k2CY3TvklE5K76K5dfH9CQH0Y=)\n[3] [medium.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHgadiZT3HeYsJc9fB3woGDAOt8L-4iB8nGLkMW2nBcGCqR3mswkmjoP8Lg40ReS4g8j7E2vq1EU3MNxoFH882UV1iao2AgStsohucS35rqQ_oqNIHRIlpKUylQiI6eEWrR0fctf-dyxVxCVTEJnJqe20Lh7W7VuQczl2qQ91zpn9FA6aTM8VA3TinpIwSbCC3d26tx8uW3X0sxOKBHnurILA-TNujfi15LOVmYuXb6D_ZFyxukXfT4e3Otk1YtG5cG1P9ruHtp)\n[4] [fortuneindia.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFCbs0uHLxnBIJIH5mrAfTVot5yu_egL40YmVMMK65yjA5aIkolQK27Flp_8hfKKW2NbYNFRZU8qoSH60C5ygyMSfiIxz8_rEwDHKmjNMxghbNqSWcQo2dxeOIVhLlhnKH3vscSTGFqQ1G6kMWXjtx6Bdpmliijut-GiCIAFKQBUAA9ZNdqk_QzjwFlezri7kmcq--Qv9Z9Y6AGkhDUGKi6X-YMZQpkQIRWu4y-JWY=)\n[5] [smestreet.in](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH8qvvNaq83NHzq3W2jEeghBXKQBZMjeFJabTXBdVagoOxlR-8LHWvDATwmxc2ZSbmuLOTRrbt4_qJpJsoxsvVsj3Ocp275hY6TIKKUXJf20-ok8ioFcy042ykp-PKTp1GD0rpOTl5HisFahwG4dKSsFvqHmR3P2Ew_zTTz5HfT0xoAnMKyGvSGB4K-kpMopHl8UBydYb518Q==)\n[6] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEtJ45FvZjrfwstHIVPb1xaGSQ3juKbCzmRX3AeYfY4CeyDfOjqLg921NKD-Fvi2b_-fDzoeH2KS3vVZNO7tuKIpe2jzM2PA9MI95f5813KyD2uHhzjdbwg_D6XSujV1nEl4i04shgiBR0ZmRg2CZKLKJ9CAXm8Zf4D)\n[7] [jsdelivr.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFDpjBZ7slHBD2FsuaxBejOlNNrfyHub1dKml5Ux9tdGYna2tw3Br0RfyKusvqxrElBTr8whWY9NRcQvmyyKp6mjURmra3bXLcPSbIbHjhbm1gIAeTHll-SvfcOmSZn7WS4Rwldh4roRFyt)\n[8] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEnziMqLa4ntGjLN5Zu1n7DanetkTEKtOAvjonySpBs3-TV5aRzwX5FXjfy02WjD6fyWsmSDhwNnNGK1InhzwfwINSiBq4ndIS7faDIwV1jhO46uSug8WtXVext)"
    search_type: SEARCH_WEB_TYPE_WEB
