      title: "apify.com"
    }
    summary: "The \"swiggy-mcp-server-manifest\" refers to Swiggy\'s implementation of the Model Context Protocol (MCP), an open standard designed to enable AI agents and chatbots to securely interact with external applications and live services. Swiggy has exposed its core commerce functionalities\342\200\224Food delivery, Instamart (grocery), and Dineout (table reservations)\342\200\224through three distinct MCP servers, collectively represented by this manifest.[1][2][3]\n\n**How it Works:**\nThe Swiggy MCP system allows AI models to understand natural language user requests and translate them into structured actions that interact directly with Swiggy\'s platform.[2][3] This means users can issue intent-based commands (e.g., \"Order ingredients for Thai green curry\") without navigating traditional app interfaces. The AI agent, acting as a tool provider, orchestrates multi-step flows such as searching, comparing options, building a cart, applying offers, and placing orders.[1][3] The protocol is permission-based, ensuring AI agents only call predefined tools and cannot directly access internal databases or payment systems, with security and validation remaining with Swiggy\'s backend.[2] This initiative is part of the Swiggy Builders Club, an ecosystem program for developers and enterprises.[1][4][5]\n\n**API Endpoints:**\nSwiggy provides three primary MCP server endpoints, each serving a different vertical of its business:\n*   **Food:** `mcp.swiggy.com/food` - For restaurant discovery, menus, ordering, and delivery tracking.[1][6]\n*   **Instamart:** `mcp.swiggy.com/im` - For quick-commerce grocery product search and ordering.[1][6]\n*   **Dineout:** `mcp.swiggy.com/dineout` - For finding restaurants, checking slot availability, and booking tables.[1][6]\n\nThese servers use streamable HTTP transport and a standard JSON-RPC format. Authentication is handled via OAuth 2.1 with PKCE.[1][6][5]\n\n**Tools:**\nAcross the three servers, Swiggy exposes a total of 35 tools (or actions) that AI agents can utilize.[1][7][5] These tools cover a wide range of functionalities:\n*   **Food Delivery:** Searching restaurants by cuisine, name, or dish; browsing menus; managing carts (adding/customizing items); and placing orders (currently supports Cash on Delivery - COD only) with order tracking.[6][8]\n*   **Instamart:** Searching products by name, category, or brand; managing carts; and seamless checkout (currently supports COD only).[6][8]\n*   **Dineout:** Discovering nearby restaurants; browsing menus and offers; checking slot availability; and instant table booking (supports free bookings only).[6][8]\n\n**Related Tools and Integrations:**\nThe Swiggy MCP architecture is designed for integration with various AI development and client tools:\n*   **AI Agent Frameworks:** Developers can build agents using SDKs like OpenAI Agents SDK, Anthropic SDK, LangGraph, Vercel AI SDK, Mastra, PydanticAI, CrewAI, or Google ADK to interact with Swiggy\'s MCP servers.[1][5]\n*   **AI Clients:** Swiggy MCP can be integrated into AI clients such as Claude Desktop, ChatGPT, Cursor, VS Code, and Windsurf, allowing users to interact with Swiggy services directly within these platforms.[1][6][5]\n*   **`swiggy-cli`:** An unofficial, community-built command-line interface provides a wrapper around the Swiggy MCP servers for developers to interact with them from the terminal.[9]\n*   **LobeHub:** This platform allows users to install Swiggy MCP servers through a quick import of a JSON configuration.[10]\n*   **Apify:** Offers \"Swiggy Restaurant Scraper\" and \"Swiggy Delivery Restaurants & Menu Scraper\" as MCP servers, enabling programmatic extraction of restaurant and menu data.[11][12]\n*   **VideoSDK AI Agent Framework:** Can be used to build voice-powered AI agents that connect to Swiggy\'s MCP servers for hands-free ordering and booking.[8]\n\nSources:\n[1] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHxDNCyQUvoNesZbrl6ariaHCuFu7MOuwE8gZf5nUri2QKrhnBCRcGJ6DJxd-s0NZ5ZdjTtMDx1W9uuptOgYoNqcIrbWgqpcjy0RjiwellxO-MH87zqtB_VzI_tzrtKoq_htq_nS6hteziA-64iT9oX-oLbZ-tdXA6Y)\n[2] [youtube.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFZTijPTSbTl4zZJNTPN4hMNKfBGmydOnMsf1OYINsR-LdwA5lq3LmgGq8bhJ2GFT3Vm2eVnvegXDTrM57OhVI1flw6syyXkDYRcHv3gaR-ZinccEysR6OKPRCmJSsx0qUuXoxefTM=)\n[3] [indiatimes.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHp_gubmEVMWHU97H3gUyxnidbAZE0he5XAdsdVi7Gfa3R3XgWLyfMVursDfsknr6jXqRJEMZbCtVqLerDph0ybRP98eFTWg_GxRuGFSG7gPbWdShLvEH28ixm9gVdOZL_RoAqVBOyLlQTavkMpimX3w7Bad_fbbiobldj84THkt-TQ5qskEYC483V6x_T0bMxYTAZ863D2k_LzwocyzgHrVcaIpyB6SjnzEIAVWx_lE8SgKWWjDgry8oTHQbqf1Rsq4Td8aw==)\n[4] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEg-wj2tdKNdGeVlxH3l6C5CNgdlQgIDnXqsyLZCc0jSsrL1NjnSQRsarhXFK7cQWxmYqMNwy-qymWJzefTnofU8K8Ij0lzPDKOjOTbEGLr1695fB5ue19hF7ft)\n[5] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE46zYGRvJjlJs8T0dHXZqhi7EEh6C-vEGJcHUnMAiYB3fuLgs8QXgp3XNJ8rXBdyrjRrcelWhnG8dHgjdwhtDTkEQYigLrV-2A8rpBAmgNAgikWSNSL5Ccg6eiSur1NrE=)\n[6] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFpbQ5AD_NFfcMlc3fGikb6Jug5Ro--geuMNN2bf_uIwPkNIGcHoJH18M6OOmI9KvViqJrgyu0Nw9vemvh5onWBZTWWBVrzam-yTwtcvYDpEZtz3fjjkrrFwkMTx7KtF5H9dnugz5jO7r9dyp0SDfU=)\n[7] [medium.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHEBDTz3yKGGKgDyBVfMIRP_F237P_HxguiDCzDts1nWwKg_DM3SbK9THud0OBNlcfKkbWBh661bPCVoSgWdHcG2sZcMJBB6Z_FbxSD2vasNIg8idIhFieHtShwFvcofwGEHkpZQr9RmzXLKP9OIBfsHySpoF6spFvfrLEZbvxyFmGdb_OfvqWPDfrAMQ7XKbOIcSUgBoHIdSP-7rQOu4d0l7eI_AtzxtWJfdE6oNv7F82A9yHveKHY1lhhfUXMuiE8JMvyiH4m)\n[8] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEft5r7xqYLe6Fg8XmAEQTIWXlh5PP2_J1X16PI4rig5AZnOULaEpfB2O78cy2lPcOi3pBPxmoY4Y0fQRi8XmPsA3lEJ2UERWquWZdPKMv0LROSCG8WTdFKlLMXWrLIgeJk8r5ERJ5WE7L03P4te3