    summary: "The GitHub repository `swiggy/swiggy-mcp-server-manifest` serves as a manifest for Swiggy\'s Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers, facilitating integration with various AI tools and agents[1][2][3]. While a complete, explicit list of all files and their hierarchical structure is not directly provided in the search results, several key files and directories can be inferred:\n\n**Identified Files and Directories:**\n*   **`README.md`**: This file likely exists, as indicated by a pull request titled \"Docs: Add Gemini CLI usage instructions to README\"[4]. It would typically contain documentation and usage instructions for the repository.\n*   **`.github/workflows/`**: The repository utilizes GitHub Actions for automation, which implies the presence of workflow definition files within a `.github/workflows` directory[5].\n*   **`mcp.json`**: This file is mentioned in the context of manual setup for configuring MCP servers, suggesting it holds critical configuration for the Model Context Protocol[6].\n*   **`swiggy_mcp.py`**: A quick start guide references `python swiggy_mcp.py` for logging into Swiggy, indicating a Python script related to the MCP[3].\n*   **`.env.example` and `.env`**: These files are typically used for environment variable configuration, as suggested by instructions to copy `.env.example` to `.env` during setup[3].\n\nThe repository is central to enabling third-party integrations with Swiggy\'s food delivery, Instamart, and Dineout services through defined APIs and tools[1][3]. It also includes information on OAuth redirect URIs and limitations regarding third-party app development[1].\n\nSources:\n[1] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGqKPr-LY8r_sUlQNrfSF3gZA8R-knRaAAoqxBD-jxQVETAtY00NCv837USACO0qWnIZ5VwZlsEx_CVJS4FQEuqdA2Xxu6gXiXxDDLfn-Nr54w77LvX6-rwt3qFs9lhGmNbXzYS4yqA_jRNuPZn9ZE=)\n[2] [jsdelivr.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF1d6k1xUrMLUQ2Dg3n