    summary: "The `swiggy-mcp-server-manifest` refers to a GitHub repository maintained by Swiggy, which serves as the official manifest for their Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers[1][2]. This manifest defines the configuration and capabilities of Swiggy\'s MCP servers, enabling AI agents to interact with Swiggy\'s Food, Instamart, and Dineout platforms through a set of predefined tools[3][4][5].\n\nWhile the complete file list or full contents of the YAML/JSON files are not directly provided in publicly available search snippets, a JSON configuration example related to connecting to a Swiggy MCP Server via a client like LobeHub has been identified. This snippet illustrates how the `swiggy-mcp-server-manifest` might be referenced in a client\'s `mcp.json` file for manual setup:\n\n\n\nSources:\n[1] [jsdelivr.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHUhxamXXYyHD48uXZUu_d1pdv1pobG1HXuPiFqx-9YEhMiBP-wYGLb41grIBzS_lqRHEFSPm88tVxqD7_YZrP3XupVjwHLi23EknCM0-Xz078v0NST4ABKNNjGGjzPJRt3hDo_gY7s_N9R)\n[2] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEA6blzUWBRFbqbJyBfyDlFcLBEzALar61kmII8s3PQKWRBJi9SBLwDIlXQa4EeyAUf-K9VX6UbG0CSgorZWkfaASDISdNauQRELNLyl8P1f2P7dCROQx0pb8wlROLnozMedU_VrE_AHvR-YbovUys=)\n[3] [youtube.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF8DLYgwLdJ1FD5z-ZvPbWIwNQ89h3H0lKr23v7xTr_SdCCIKLPnCb5LssGNsMgzrxZoOU-cIGP9gQ-6WkNUy6PEjabkgYFnWyLjMb-EQ7HMH--nMxvG-9md3_SkRd2z4Tfq5mOS8k=)\n[4] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGIZ5Wj3KVqnWdSswEAw4sms4lQMPoMi_SCdsWJWfbmWiMOxGNPRJm4jLnDc8Zlp5uXB2OMjoezUhk2M4WheXy0cG-OWBgitagLYPYCLKAaz1mKviNFbpSi34x_XZp6I_qtt_n_HaKtOSEjo47ieE1IEwQaBG-1yH9R)\n[5] [medium.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH5H7k0AX175n5Xn41Kjba3fJEkV9wT2BDVCxi7iaU0uVRis2o0JnwSxPK0v2SbsY6GMeiAHsPNzIJAKDyqYlnbfJpOKndakbWNwXSWkiMYUVurNY_IG1v8At9NM5HGNIM-9FP5zzH2NOkY4XRWGAj2gy9I