    summary: "The \"swiggy-mcp-server-manifest\" refers to a GitHub repository maintained by Swiggy that is related to its Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers. These MCP servers enable AI agents to interact with Swiggy\'s various services, including Instamart, Food, and Dineout.[1][2][3]\n\nFor Swiggy Instamart, the \"swiggy-mcp-server-manifest\" facilitates access to several key functionalities, which align with the keywords provided:\n*   **Search**: It allows for product searches by name, category, or brand at a given delivery location.[1]\n*   **Menu**: While not explicitly called \"menu,\" the product search and cart management features imply interaction with product listings and details.[1]\n*   **Add to Cart/Cart Management**: Users or integrated agents can view items in their cart, see pricing and bill breakdowns, add items, and customize orders.[1]\n*   **Checkout/Order**: The manifest supports seamless checkout and placing grocery orders, with instant confirmation (currently supporting Cash on Delivery).[1]\n*   **Tools**: The MCP servers expose various \"tools\" for developers to integrate with, although some issues have been reported, such as the `clear_cart` tool not always clearing the cart successfully and the `get_orders` tool sometimes returning outdated information.[4][5][6]\n\nThe \"Swiggy Builders Club\" provides documentation for developers to build AI agents that can utilize these MCP tools to incorporate commerce capabilities into their applications.[3]\n\nSources:\n[1] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEnbVXa160txo6x2dCYkEiwXic00g-iMZUgliKM478HSL2C4mCy2oaB9ZMY1NwWt4pEN5ld53Yw5GvGQE2dtDZhdpjqouynyi_z1e5MnUIg5iauJ-QV78g56VaSfvEU3cXS2lkNdC2i54YN4oSptmo=)\n[2] [jsdelivr.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHXzCpudfuxKpJQMDL5zbs3FKj5nZtCrTesH7AcsN_FlDgDon8VpcSopE_yy4SojpT-aga1LtcQ0CgevWhy6WNpAIoOoSjuCW4k34CAZivyGSp9J74mIpTT-C5MT79GFL6AUrAKRn5Srp4E)\n[3] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH93T17kME-lpl5-Kqrg4x4eeXK7gGe78Em6kyrGEWTVAtF_bHLtLc_BMMD_aTChG7juZKQAEAs0bEgypzTunBDnKVXFFUJAJcZIriHJ1NOkUlPuZ3rL6oqJGgh-5pnseY=)\n[4] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFLYUQS1PXAzWSYK4HqIh2642HKWNv9Tprnr5qyLn2hqiIfVD-gitAGDERX1jI8MIzQHLu1UJz1jc5m2ROyLPc6NcTOc4vWjipeW4hbuGIJrsbj2LPknelWZJSD_VChQWZXXA-mSFiS4QHdVIlCqKXVmrs69JfK)\n[5] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHrXG-YtbypMQAbYeHKnu9PEuPb_ifzX78547F8Vc8gGOziTLJoz6truLpq-HtunOAvzU_tXYFbB5T1agrK2xA53uMv_ZB_Jv3zlFi0I_eAz6eqhcRYLEINqjhvKsJb0q9TqIiZL-_VJzt27DC-qAJbU4Z4u4FdGz24)\n[6] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE2koE_k3lzJv4w9wWHcXvoxrYk5FtraZ7WKBeKZnxzWKQbNbKnm9qCFC__sXZY_iNXoclykG9vHAAivytpCbriedYukWUYJP36WfHR7j59mDvihQA4v2zaChUZL0OLBY1JcTxcq3-AlTAZSVYHxBlddOzXQ--lc-W0)"
