    summary: "The \"Swiggy/swiggy-mcp-server-manifest\" generally refers to a GitHub repository or a conceptual manifest for Swiggy\'s Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers[1][2].\n\nWhen looking for a file name related to this, the most relevant formats are JSON, specifically:\n*   **`mcp.json`**: This file is used for local configuration of MCP servers[1]. Manual setup often involves configuring these servers in a local `mcp.json` file[1].\n*   **JSON configuration**: An example of an MCP server configuration is provided in JSON format, where `\"swiggy-swiggy-mcp-server-manifest\"` is a key within the configuration object[1].\n*   **`auth.json`**: User authentication tokens for Swiggy MCP are stored in `~/.swiggy/auth.json`[3].\n\nWhile the context describes \"Model Context Protocol\" servers exposing various tools, and API specifications are common for such services, an explicit OpenAPI or YAML file name directly within the \"Swiggy/swiggy-mcp-server-manifest\" repository or its immediate documentation isn\'t clearly specified in the search results. The interaction with these servers often occurs via JSON-RPC calls[4].\n\nSources:\n[1] [lobehub.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHWf_Kd76EsSLPAu-nh787tldsamxmC2ewzgZeCyFIMt0yyeqmNbWxcWQJJE9GfhWqDYGzENw2MQGmwoHbKhY0Tuv72BgUgk9XJH7Vg7voK0jptCOv93dMEsv-tdYmiY-s-H4RITz5w6zzxM9Yv4DGGfvscSWwpVdIroRtFBwUF830M-RXOdvmNIA==)\n[2] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEoGIZPxOXyMrXE6fQyKiVYiSguQ8Qd0YHgn-Nh1gHvZldLGskchDNozPy9ts7yTNsG6EkHv6e4yOY9xcYfrAuB86V8VRqK17cIFoxT1V9YWn0gvHG7p-5VOX4aYsjbnY3x9eqfBOEAt98qVSXW6O8=)\n[3] [jsdelivr.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEgEb3_iwrVqFUOl9XdDH9Ly2dJKiz32mc9C1eqXAqifZkopTULOii2pvgsVs1G6IZNSNAWtFH0avjoZBdWr9Yb6txGG1plGbVQrDpZ2Bsr1P2r0PIgks4cnwG6NSNrWuIFvbWkoVD6N_-3)\n[4] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEHotulgBy9tU-8