    summary: "Swiggy\'s Model Context Protocol (MCP) server manifests are primarily managed within a dedicated public GitHub repository: `Swiggy/swiggy-mcp-server-manifest`[1][2][3]. This repository serves as a central location for development and information related to Swiggy\'s MCP server implementations.\n\nFor **Instamart**, a specific URL or endpoint for its MCP server is `https://mcp.swiggy.com/im`[1][4][5][6][7][8].\n\nRegarding file formats, both **JSON** and **YAML** are supported and commonly used for configuring MCP servers and their manifests[5][9]. While the specific manifest files might reside within the `Swiggy/swiggy-mcp-server-manifest` GitHub repository, the context of MCP integrations and related tools indicates that configuration data is often exchanged or defined in these formats. For instance, an example of an MCP server configuration provided for LobeHub uses a JSON structure[5]. The `swiggy-cli` also indicates that the underlying McpClient communicates using Streamable-HTTP MCP, which supports JSON[10].\n\nSources:\n[1] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGnvSKstb4_jHLr9aa3E0xbfKBWYq7j9yCiA4Wdfd3DXxKkoqZ9tf2Nj58AigxAYwBIRU6rnHn7AaYyB4IXVxurxNa1c6Bmoek_rzL1fGqvjHSQNkjQR7hrAHzDuCsUnT80iBccI2RlDWNGVtJod8w=)\n[2] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHkNt2ppjS6Mn_qoDSjaooB9SfxVXfA9GP-loVkqL-T-1FDg9IvZXQO7sdDzvn0YSDpco6QaxV4O5NYWR_oMcRspya6OdoLekU-y9iJ9axQGaBi-H8=)\n[3] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEAZ7MfjNoGRJaCyHJRS4wrGZr1p8K-06OaScflyYjf7p-j42o5I53NMUWcANeZyCYLYejj_6sTmAs84M23g33QP1ix1n9G6b9Q_CgjZr5MdJ0Dwi_ngWW9zosE3Sdl5qhwincrfHm3holPUjZwO_Nv7661i5TkJWRa)\n[4] [medium.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFSbaE77INEC0MP4utF0iZ5RrDkFXuCKMTU3rqcNw7vfniBMG6G_Pj8CM-K-TQgiTyW1t3fqxTerA1ZCqRbmVZiK1hEWBR0GK2e1VumELmHqS0xlHZfeX8OwZLQMve-B_PVRZCQEDumEnzpu0csPyCPVaOTb9_LAUvUwni