    web_documents {
      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHitWG0ruFaRnS60s670mDlZSQNWh9aNa_JnUmuuppLvBXTYY3DMxJeJpR-IasB5ZsfNiyT-FZIxn-T3q6b58ecxSknGOULnE1qkyBo411J5bhYlyqOIzLyWwqYl6hoJlfPY0EsHss3iHvHT35_yZ83j28hkOEOeArT1CuUvE5zWG-s"
      title: "apple.com"
    }
    summary: "Swiggy has launched Model Context Protocol (MCP) integrations across its various business verticals, including Swiggy Food, Instamart, and Dineout. This enables users to order groceries, place food orders, and make dining reservations directly through popular AI tools like ChatGPT, Claude, and Google Gemini[1]. Instamart, Swiggy\'s quick-commerce platform, is reportedly the first globally to adopt MCP, allowing users to browse and purchase over 40,000 SKUs using natural language prompts[1].\n\nThe Model Context Protocol (MCP) is an open-source framework designed to connect AI systems and chatbots to live data, sources, and services, facilitating secure interaction with external applications[1]. By exposing a secure set of tools via MCP servers, Swiggy allows AI agents to perform complex tasks that would otherwise require navigating multiple app screens[1]. Users can issue intent-based commands, such as \"Order ingredients needed for Thai green curry\" or \"Order a highly rated biryani I would love\"[1].\n\nSwiggy\'s MCP launch is intended to lay the groundwork for future AI-led experiences, where intelligent agents can act contextually across use cases like meal planning, health goals, dietary preferences, and occasion-based shopping, all while prioritizing privacy and security[1]. Swiggy is also launching the \"Builders Club,\" a program for developers and enterprises to build AI-native commerce experiences on its platforms, providing access to APIs, MCP servers, and transactional capabilities across Food, Instamart, and Dineout[2]. The Builders Club will initially open access to 3 MCP servers and over 18 API tools[2].\n\nThe `swiggy-mcp-server-manifest` on GitHub provides details on the functionalities available through the MCP for Swiggy Food and Instamart. For Swiggy Food, this includes restaurant search, menu browsing, cart management, and food ordering with cash on delivery (COD) support. For Instamart, it offers product search, cart management, and grocery order placement, also with COD support[3]. It also notes current limitations, such as the prohibition of third-party app development at this time due to ongoing security reviews[3].\n\nInstamart itself is an instant grocery delivery service launched by Swiggy in August 2020, utilizing a network of dark stores[4]. As of 2025, Swiggy operates Instamart in 100 cities[4]. It allows users to order groceries and other essentials, with services like instant grocery delivery and free delivery for Swiggy One users[5]. Instamart is present in over 120 cities and operates from 6 a.m. to late at night, with timings varying by city[5].\n\nSources:\n[1] [indiatimes.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQErxNkiDWBySeeNpvoeR4mqfhnG3HPksBv5ZrqOjP5Av-Z1N3W7mifUcKgSzNTsGFVl6WqZaG3OMDuobQtO6_sgR4qwwJ-9VBTaaR30YCnKexX4tPRy4b2xtNa3zdQUQUbHwhx1P67f4V-hIQFmHv4xyuzBODJTNOay02uzSLVuD40-KxkabALgNWvMiYbXCnXDPAIv_nRWaMNL2cOEpP3gMnCU1PU7SrJK-5gXSfxzXYXIkKdkqLJnUzopCM_gwrNZWtRt_w==)\n[2] [aboutamazon.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEWlsY-5HZDVNKGgPaBJyPVW5xW4kjTx3bOFzGGKn24sO5Hrib_DJ4EmSZ64V_gVu5Dwk7zU6PsrD9Z1B70AIAgQaTyXHDm396kcbRhvENK3ABq2LtRy-HImRY2ECIiw6GrrInmsuYT-vIDNyko_CQ-p7E_uql6-kMnx7BwnreN0IJ-LuAPrCvZ-2f6xL7Vrm-SJIk82XP6AcUo-FUmL45OyxKB6hp8SeyoZZHuX5neoWc75t1g5HaX0TEnc-l4H6b4JuYoRw==)\n[3] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEp61S43ctmvRiJr0thFJYh4N6rMnFQqObqLyPClypZJoexmDcQlnXHXMGd6r3HXweV8ZxtiPA0UlUSoL3PmswRcqLXV9R_Zt_S9IVVAxBxBqFpvpU1TvQZIvyTIzcwlMnx-b9v2a70u8kfNLQA3gc=)\n[4] [wikipedia.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGvis6zZEmziur8SFASNgC7c9JcP7FWyGnz_l2N8Z94_ZDpW2DZDTppsppXEeWoZXipidRnKZHDd4iYhSSvfmyu1sUwuwtmMNDnQ4bIXsletw-TtvpZQwDkI8E6rwtMig==)\n[5] [apple.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHitWG0ruFaRnS60s670mDlZSQNWh9aNa_JnUmuuppLvBXTYY3DMxJeJpR-IasB5ZsfNiyT-FZIxn-T3q6b58ecxSknGOULnE1qkyBo411J5bhYlyqOIzLyWwqYl6hoJlfPY0EsHss3iHvHT35_yZ83j28hkOEOeArT1CuUvE5zWG-s)"
    search_type: SEARCH_WEB_TYPE_WEB
