    summary: "Swiggy has integrated and exposed its commerce platform as \"Model Context Protocol\" (MCP) servers, enabling developers to build AI agents that can interact with Swiggy\'s services.[1][2][3] This initiative, launched through the \"Swiggy Builders Club,\" provides access to Swiggy Food, Instamart, and Dineout functionalities via MCP.[2][3]\n\nHere are the key details regarding Swiggy\'s MCP servers and API:\n\n**Server Endpoints and Tools:**\nSwiggy exposes its services through three distinct MCP servers, each with its own endpoint and a set of tools:\n*   **Food:** `mcp.swiggy.com/food` \342\200\223 Offers 14 tools for restaurant discovery, menu browsing, cart management, and food ordering.[4][3][5][6]\n*   **Instamart:** `mcp.swiggy.com/im` \342\200\223 Provides 13 tools for product search, cart management, and grocery order placement.[4][3][5][6]\n*   **Dineout:** `mcp.swiggy.com/dineout` \342\200\223 Includes 8 tools for restaurant discovery, details, slot availability, and table booking.[4][3][5][6]\n\nThese endpoints utilize a POST method for making calls.[5]\n\n**Protocol and Authentication:**\n*   Swiggy\'s MCP implementation is built on the Model Context Protocol, an open standard that facilitates integration between large language model (LLM) applications and external tools and data sources.[2][3][7][8]\n*   The communication happens over streamable HTTP using standard JSON-RPC.[3][9]\n*   Authentication is handled via OAuth 2.1 with Proof Key for Code Exchange (PKCE).[4][2][3][6][9] A single Bearer token, scoped to `mcp:tools`, is issued and works across all three servers.[4]\n*   Supported OAuth Redirect URIs include `http://localhost`, `http://localhost/callback`, `https://chatgpt.com/connector_platform_oauth_redirect`, and others for various AI clients like Claude and VS Code.[6]\n\n**API Capabilities and Development:**\n*   The MCP servers allow AI agents to perform complex tasks such as searching for products or restaurants, comparing options, building and updating carts, applying offers, placing orders, and tracking deliveries.[1][7]\n*   Developers can integrate Swiggy MCP into various AI agent frameworks, including OpenAI Agents SDK, Anthropic, LangGraph, Vercel AI SDK, Mastra, CrewAI, and Google ADK.[2][3]\n*   Swiggy provides a \"Builders Club\" with documentation, recipes, and a reference guide to all 35 tools, parameters, and error codes.[2][5][9]\n*   While Swiggy exposes these servers for integration, third-party app development is currently not permitted due to ongoing security reviews and compliance requirements.[6]\n*   A GitHub repository, `swiggy-mcp-server-manifest`, is available under the Swiggy GitHub organization, which likely contains reference documentation for their MCP implementation.[10][11][12]\n\nSources:\n[1] [indiatimes.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHWqpSd2dYfhXcj6S1QnApNUhTOdOtMrveCMn6UKHXcdZBjDfQFiS4GQT6Racjz5hUqt4c4v_NtIvDTB0xTY1lcsrRX5_2Kwn6_8Kk42b0-TKyYbJYwhR4sb3toYBfKH33w1MjWTz8xPnlE05KadPSEoC2RcSbzV-y0wOr00kpkr-4UoztLpXhwIoHBQYORz8lRafmPPnefR6lX31m2z6qlQkm8XllLPN9xWDxOyesZH50SQtfIR1sjgjUH75hTbGQHVZDn)\n[2] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEuzt1iMHiDLIIHz8fAyxCh3_EzWMRH6qC6Jy6FsSFhzRv0ToJ4JdafVRxiFF4_iD6kjbbIPYCQEGx6VMrW_weYQ6Sqc1vopme41eHlzT32AmRAWtqFKq4IruIKd3jRfQ==)\n[3] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEOQjRMun-04ru2CBNJ36QioFQWxxK60u9U818PFYMx3csSHcVPgKbbw_hXy0DQdGPQ612avcPCMcWKoSA01c14323cKjUL0xKyvRffcJodfLBIqoZH5XOxIqqLipTUvxxPYCjpJX5UX342CVqNmcxY8JKL7l6GQi8=)\n[4] [medium.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHegEQO2lSRZUZGa-ES6cT3-NFE_FS3vNNQSORsWT9tzuRDR0u1yVK6CHODjN3CDm3Z3xf2S5D7bAJekbY10OumMW0FKqzeBPbyaOFd1UHLNzbPBQ39L66uNlPhV2teCf9hjzyMMUMWA2FvHkRhjKc5IbFZLm2DK7qVSv5LPS6BzQ6D4QiqEHl4mlDq2luiy2erEOgb6g1p-X4N4QVLBJjBvScUktvJCl19DFu0tF9zVUObx027piKTEbfcwovgcVaOLlPKmBU=)\n[5] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGmCVqTu9a95HJahGPBkSmYG3AMphgvxCPniBRxaNqNYyF_axD1QH7W82e9-gDx4V-4gV9zyUXvxchoXrEABsR02clxBeDZdfMb7A9wpPIKP1WYQFMla0drs3Tw6olsvbwDdvzWUVjCYuo=)\n[6] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG0IpuSAm8gL6HvYtf2jFSuWeMf3wopfwGM6TTAb-O_F-gfPrd6CvIkKeeUIm2Muq6ee2NY1JMDSpRbZOpItrTiRHsmNn47esRDC-xePa4D3u6PU7DiTofchsfygm5gDx0YTcXCylH8gyNJDQFBTA==)\n[7] [exchange4media.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGJkmcGA2cpV4CTYxMhsrfn7El43AynKhpfquth5eTgWm1q2AUwo6MscO0G6vG8q7yhdaKhmFYn_n5bvA5UuHw9gBHDZ8H-Bp5VRV0scVUBXRE1SZw8Cj1MsJfHm8dzlWxskCgh8Ci88pWMX-mr7E7fT89Be_-kVoIkcZdTyMrsbqyvPku7BuzHhW22rkvkhMhyAHE6ZYzw_IYrvB-URjb5F4nty7lUWcDNlQcdZK9qjLUfKbFZJxxFJFesySEdQskbLrMjEwmqqrwGg-67TeBSQKac)\n[8] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEF5WfDL9MERMJ0ApL1-C4vYGnYxXJGfn-5HmDNAW7XaL2U7d8T_BykJrbMk08jtg8jrqNklrUrN4kSKAADqD2soMocqH6kbdrEcVaT9FjMzR-fa1ZR_98mCovjKc5ICRNI)\n[9] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFS5IG4gcfDwKwiE1Ld8vkXVWXFcceTIBBg36_zi0zQUOd7-Fy2S3iJh7qLDMf1cTipUqQZN1xzg4g0FcvOUCsyHfgzEZSnqGChqfmEjtnmk3dyg6UV_0sXJbQZh16sXWoIv0XGeDHuRDvks4ceY_w=)\n[10] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEfMb296XPKH5LxxDccvUn4-JkbbIW-lQgNMLAHdCGaLyGPL7uIx-sVe6VMfRz3dIyq3CG8FCZK_NSplqcn8oZd9ZxugQP5My_h5iCKA2AwgJKSrJjGiFIBcE-YWBTtMV4GrYs7-WueZCat6yluwcm8J71dDbSKAAqY8G8yyw==)\n[11] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGQ8JmOFhLQt3hs9nYjEPwq9vYIJS2tygeykRJNYAufDvGdTIs-WrDfs3UpgZwbJwXVipV8G5IVQuuTkpS7PXyZH1ytezSlie02owe8fLxnXc8IDRcDQSREOx1vObNkUrk71ovGsA==)\n[12] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEusLuBjPq-JT97rm8TvcieNObFYb8qIyMRcxdM-LBVLDIN976SCVu9s2OFcQhWI3cSbtju0872z7kES0flCZ2-VnbaJSPU1JCvZXbTt__xVcFL4Q==)"
