    summary: "The search on medium.com/swiggy-engineering for \"mcp\" OR \"Model Context\" OR \"Protocol\" OR \"server\" did not yield any results directly from Swiggy Engineering\'s Medium page. However, the search results provided extensive information about the \"Model Context Protocol (MCP)\".\n\nThe Model Context Protocol (MCP) is an open standard and open-source framework introduced by Anthropic in November 2024. It aims to standardize the way AI systems, such as large language models (LLMs), integrate and share data with external tools, systems, and data sources[1][2][3]. Think of MCP as a \"USB-C port for AI applications,\" providing a standardized way to connect AI with various external systems[4].\n\nKey aspects of MCP include:\n*   **Purpose**: It allows AI applications like Claude or ChatGPT to connect to data sources (e.g., local files, databases), tools (e.g., search engines, calculators), and workflows (e.g., specialized prompts), enabling them to access information and perform tasks[4].\n*   **Functionality**: MCP provides a standardized interface for reading files, executing functions, and handling contextual prompts[1]. It addresses the limitations of LLMs, such as their knowledge being static at training time and their inability to interact with the outside world[3].\n*   **Architecture**: The MCP architecture involves an MCP host (the AI application or environment), an MCP client (within the host, facilitating communication), and an MCP server (the external service providing context, data, or capabilities)[3]. Communication between the client and server primarily uses JSON-RPC 2.0 messages over a transport layer[3].\n*   **Benefits**: MCP reduces development time and complexity for developers building or integrating with AI applications. For AI applications, it provides access to an ecosystem of data sources, tools, and apps, enhancing capabilities. End-users benefit from more capable AI applications that can access their data and take actions on their behalf[4].\n*   **Adoption**: Following its announcement, MCP was adopted by major AI providers, including OpenAI and Google DeepMind[1]. Companies like Microchip Technology are also utilizing MCP servers to provide real-time access to their product data, documentation, and inventory through natural language queries[5].\n\nSources:\n[1] [wikipedia.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE_yc2r2fHKXaTGNADz96Spy0HkIfDtYf3rAxprY5YU49xUaAMBdNGpDyDh-reCrPPOx1oBiAHF41DdhfSOTHbVmsrbxvwubwDt4rRI9DwlgAWKzgviwa0dNpBU1vMPhxiW6UEfPH_hlPjidLSXUw==)\n[2] [anthropic.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGC5rkRqHuC_KLXjH-XCuMOwp6rwhbwzamW65KZQ8n0gT3kPxhbsx-dAFqY6WkH5xSJie4nhvpOeQIoZjiYFjiV-U658FxKymHot7SLgMsAUYjZhomYdm5hw0YHZBv3aFMaDb2p7Ii48AhrVgcplD0=)\n[3] [google.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFEi_0YHp_uHrfUg1rTiV0uDIm7W6hmZMRtYk3fj6TijEEf97ves7VBFYxOPuldx1FzEiCOIMfcF6X6WktfqdPrGnrv0MR7AAPmU2Y5P7ZtGcMweIqh2x7jakQ66ePQI0Z-F96M__yc4a4PhLfq5q8PGCOkvpykHDB7Yw==)\n[4] [modelcontextprotocol.io](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGnOHK5lLg7mFPXUy8YMyMDNcdAkYPwM9iqSHP2szG6GPN7qFiDyAZzHSLcWHCAIyM83FsteWRK2aE86uEQjrbCzJvfSkCODQEXusvXhqXhA-5hjLHfz2G7DTw5KXyl0FqFtbIJXUhXDpRC-n6TetRWghVEJQ==)\n[5] [microchip.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHqK1DLw5QSAXb3NBHv9z7KHTi27So0vxlQZn7D0tpkdZ1LYv7ZewikOptGxouTIXy6gx2INDLOsIVTZh_vRVs0if_5qVc5uWWSPWkk5dzMBq4wTTJ3WSvauJ3FJqrNzuK6LCx_HYTZTmMKJAe8KgRbClx-zBJ-gj6QEAIUAUBSx1I=)"
