    summary: "A search for `site:github.com/Swiggy/swiggy-mcp-server-manifest inurl:main` reveals the GitHub repository belonging to Swiggy for their Model Context Protocol (MCP) server manifest[1]. While the `inurl:main` specifier typically refers to a \"main\" branch within a repository, search results confirm the existence of the `Swiggy/swiggy-mcp-server-manifest` repository[1]. GitHub repositories commonly utilize \"main\" as their default or primary branch.\n\nThis repository is associated with Swiggy\'s Model Context Protocol (MCP) integrations, which enable AI tools like ChatGPT, Claude, and Google Gemini to interact with Swiggy\'s services for ordering food, groceries, and making dining reservations[2]. The project aims to allow AI agents to perform tasks that would typically require navigating multiple app screens, by exposing a secure set of tools via MCP servers[2]. Another related project demonstrates a Swiggy voice AI agent built using the VideoSDK Agent Framework, which integrates with the Swiggy MCP server manifest[3].\n\nSources:\n[1] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFcTMKisX7eEa51ZFkS_PqFLcMwAENJrLONqqCuyTDfz4rZQ8biYRwu0PH1n_KJYhZ--6ayNm5iPHMNqIGKVEVpz84dZo-IwOjuEjBO5tQ5QyIW8Up71zk_lDDGi6hlqCoCh9FFG2rqzNLuh6cCVCE=)\n[2] [chennaipatrika.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG1mPLhFqLXjRsJfZmZOjuNX79TzSi4DH8CBAoufTmp8FinAC1SgJY_y7fov73pW7KRHTggM2PSjsTaCWEQNMqXd9ADjOP7w6_cVih713r_PTk0n6ztFzDRqFrBHMBr_16Pv9tQe6WT_9JjyJyMbGfRPAa9fUz0vIly0r87DXMTG2PbPTn8R1vEmdgDQRIzxOYHdCgRYWK9qllVI67S66U1KtrHmrMdVMcA0ym-cZBu0p9pwW0WDwkXm3g=)\n[3] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG6eBYcOfg49CHwRW_H6B9ybs57BXD-S8BjrnVKfbfG_l6js74Hl9QfNlTZ_1CmiInVegR4nx7ijmX-K9gK3RZ8lQgIoNtX9eMWQMIxkf9t153nsWGFI7DdJ4tRF27jSZEOMGG02xHU-NaGIjvaH83Ut2z7jEcajV2LcSLztpQ=)"
