    summary: "The \"Swiggy/swiggy-mcp-server-manifest\" is a GitHub repository that defines Swiggy\'s Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers[1][2][3]. This repository primarily contains the manifest for three distinct MCP servers: Food, Instamart, and Dineout[2][3]. These servers expose a total of 35 tools that allow AI agents to interact with Swiggy\'s commerce platform, enabling functions like discovering restaurants, ordering groceries, tracking deliveries, and booking tables[1][2][4][3][5].\n\nThe key document for understanding this repository is its `README.md` file, which can be found directly on GitHub[6]. This README provides an overview of the MCP, its functionalities, and how AI models and developers can integrate with Swiggy\'s services through these defined tools[1][6][2][7][5]. The repository facilitates the integration of Swiggy\'s services into various AI tools and agent frameworks[2][7][5].\n\nSources:\n[1] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFDjw_IJXRrTYvDkxxPiwvzyn7rEYhxmqhYTy7zEd9v_CfkHd-x4MegQwAEpc80oShloVBYHl269xpBxRL5eyO3-XtJCQ4NNiABIKMPoLVfx0iLryDvf7PeYxEllE80IuqvUk5WUP1iaAg8HAHrUiY=)\n[2] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHRuHIcrsoPGyGn07RQO6r89otNVxReCnbB1EAv0MskUp5e2MzLzd6i2Mik3ui9RBo7c5QSZT8Q3lGk1ukYAT6en5QeAn2313C6P3V4cWujDVxGAdvCsk2tjp_3N319GCk4dLKKSJzsVix7c8g4lSKVReKP4l8khE59)\n[3] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE9jsUYqvtbRda49fSLwbYJj7UVfXYqUzMSY6NO1Z51ngrEtVuTpHB0xyQrsSUKAN1UBFJn1xL70VkZcJkGaIWWeRO5W6dUJZoBfw-2GnFLIl-CbFFGFBVw2DbkV_n4cZU=)\n[4] [medium.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEzjPqrmHSG1AyQ9GS3wdILihBDPZkDudhAUqwObJT5KTQgy79tGWq_LHLRoNnv9f8mYIsALlKjsNAiXSHJUjmGVfixfI-4c_6rDu_GF8BpwuggedX8ANoe_tjv3n7Bfjd3Q69GnKUO9B5phYtIvirx1d6H61qIe3iX1-0GW6BODSLpWEFOvrCeXKvvOiKgzdGQMIecJiRLC05P8B19kACoMhlSHqNRCw0UFgbJet8weExOl0kWr90TVOjKy8ZENreXwdmh6Ahw)\n[5] [