      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFJGfFIaxKmhQAlKSY7fyB1OuQQQOIMBxoUePqVVovNF7At5yp0cfp_IIlMP2lm1x-C_Q3lG7Kt-Rswk_WEgNO7n0O_IzL0C27GggiHlPn7ZGa-R0pmA81GJGWvUsQakxb-Jz3NdnPqPWTuCt2k24S50IRxBsUQEiiDiMIT7TnsRjLipmgtVlCB"
      title: "lobehub.com"
    }
    summary: "The GitHub repository `github.com/Swiggy/swiggy-mcp-server-manifest` serves as the official manifest and documentation for Swiggy\'s Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers[1][2]. This repository provides details on how to interact with Swiggy\'s commerce platform through AI agents and other applications using the open-standard MCP[1][3][4][5].\n\nKey aspects of the `swiggy-mcp-server-manifest` repository and Swiggy\'s MCP implementation include:\n*   **Purpose of MCP** The Model Context Protocol (MCP) is an open-source framework that allows AI systems and chatbots to securely connect and interact with external applications, live data, and services[6][3][4].\n*   **Swiggy\'s MCP Servers** Swiggy exposes its services through three distinct MCP servers:\n    *   **Food:** Enables restaurant discovery, menu browsing, food ordering, and order tracking, offering 14 tools for these functionalities[1][3][7].\n    *   **Instamart:** Facilitates quick-commerce grocery ordering with 13 dedicated tools[1][3][7].\n    *   **Dineout:** Provides 8 tools for making table reservations at restaurants[1][3][7].\n*   **Functionality for AI Agents** Through these MCP servers, AI agents can execute complex tasks via natural language prompts. This includes searching for items or restaurants, comparing options, managing shopping carts, applying offers, confirming addresses, placing orders, and booking tables[1][3][8][4].\n*   **Target Users** The platform is designed for developers creating AI agents using various SDKs (e.g., OpenAI Agents SDK, Anthropic SDK, LangGraph), large-scale agent platforms, and users of AI clients such as Claude Desktop, ChatGPT, Cursor, and VS Code[1][3].\n*   **Integration and Usage**\n    *   Authentication is handled via the standard OAuth 2.1 with PKCE[2][3][7].\n    *   Users connect to the MCP servers through specific HTTP endpoints like `https://mcp.swiggy.com/food`, `https://mcp.swiggy.com/im`, and `https://mcp.swiggy.com/dineout`[1][9][6][3][7].\n    *   A community-developed command-line interface, `swiggy-cli`, is available to simplify interaction with these MCP servers[2].\n    *   Important usage notes indicate that users should avoid having the Swiggy mobile application open simultaneously with MCP integrations to prevent session conflicts[1][2]. Additionally, cash-on-delivery (COD) orders placed via MCP cannot be canceled[1][2].\n\nSources:\n[1] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGkW3VFCmSeo8RXtmaA4wUniG5_ch8b_Sw1F5rQ4liaNSVOLZrR_F20PfkI1iCEZ-kT3G8o1_pAIGVr8mevS9GIx2dPhxR5Kz5Ls1mnSXCH0zSAkG4tULu73THRyuNv5mQ4CtjZ_9jglTBC5rnVrA==)\n[2] [jsdelivr.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFuP_rhwQsuWjbMaZ7H8mHPxH1sv-pe3hyH7BWpazEc2rWM74qJU5IjY2Eiv3WWtDgZHncwJ0vxkd8kjI-gEn481Tsl8PqTluiTle2A_ZRKQG8g61s8Na0xWqtpVY5kLE-4BDCvxBU8CKo=)\n[3] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF17aN_bpGl4Hmi-meq3tiAiP9XSEzqX1Cji2gCi0htiV2fE7ekpzwztLMXf11q_bZh3B5g1OicaZIcAD-F1O6pmOg8eE_emqIQWcroodvbYEhS75DjMu9Sa-yTrvFNlQYFaYTXZu4gnfZNlQ2PSs2GGnCAm-vkEtM=)\n[4] [indiatimes.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEUl7nfgmNX0AUobmcDPWYvUtkZHreIqBDoq3KGLLc5UxkcRVf-tYx4mpkTdG_-kDFu8n_5iN-1FiNol9Q0CfoBC5K5i7O4aCicw2DF6LG0CjJOMgRRKF-3HVh78rlnSQkB6aSOaQmt5M9k6hFg-GnaxDHrrZUNRmWEi5Qht06vROp6cMDKqcbDdV6vzb3XGEQXqyqBEgeGn6tctzwHujmvmPbftFgTayaAnUTfc4jK63qkzdLU_TYMnDaFGvlXojW92glL)\n[5] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFM6e6DYvTUKMilU_RjBgGaOZrtM_7m7F5GJeTEk1U0tjhTo2Lgl6MTKEBxTgweGWd5vzErPNhQal8EHcLBfe_QME6hPzXIbi2dYO8bKSk7o1eVhF2MWS59y6c=)\n[6] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFQ06RXTHddnyo05SU9GBAtzEXyz8Ndy3i84RZ1qzGv14mPZtGUBk4RGLcyzwG5NMobsPoRLFeoIpX2ziMPiGSsBqYT75v63-VPpzrXhsP-Y1PsHuARduCv1Zz-vtf8KgxVf8BS7uxp8GsB)\n[7] [medium.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE6FiyjNIKyUylvgwOpf9fjlRvxduNv_GUj6hxkY7eMaHbghU6-dEMkmyPYCQlkKvd4Q0F-pym65gXcHX_nMAyuFJMkD4587HXiYIEvvOvis1oI88OpHea149MlGIKYn7YjOQYAU3KTPNM2DMFeHSeZdMeDvkE3wfwZlOSfu1R7_jz0DkkyZWYKk4IeB_TXy8ngLbN4H37PM-sdcCKFWUH-ZMpkTa73NTj5tYeYM9KqtgIEr7GPl-txMfUqiF7prLZszrSnk7M=)\n[8] [youtube.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHz3EgfXQrVayfiNgcdSHb0UmKobKKx5g6WxBg-yiDTGdsj9f-9TSg3HTwWN5c2VNxPOiRDSdNozHERhWF7V88clZQD2gGrVm0ciL7yr7sUgE5KrfAvWDAUtaMKAfIl3QC16egJEQ==)\n[9] [lobehub.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFJGfFIaxKmhQAlKSY7fyB1OuQQQOIMBxoUePqVVovNF7At5yp0cfp_IIlMP2lm1x-C_Q3lG7Kt-Rswk_WEgNO7n0O_IzL0C27GggiHlPn7ZGa-R0pmA81GJGWvUsQakxb-Jz3NdnPqPWTuCt2k24S50IRxBsUQEiiDiMIT7TnsRjLipmgtVlCB)"
