      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGKqTZg_TeFpGQnoYvjVLsiHWh6jXjNF8UvS8Dn9RTd_whzSdOkYQLuQ84bRcFMd_41G9nlu-Utcd9wf7Z1jzjFc-ImKsvNoPexHAocrY6wiDZeVBQn_w9Y2YRl"
      title: "swiggy.com"
    }
    web_documents {
      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHQ6wpqyHsVdHbWMRMx6PLrY963dAECBKWRmBVn05SM6OydTRNKmxBguT0EZxqSocFbgOHIOVFn72iwNTrv-K-2Lo9xzsDF7p2C-73kky4RWBX7viD5JhrK52fWBEvOrIW4MyDFDGBfZmoM3owx-F76g4wIgbpjeObQngKYyLGUDyo="
      title: "instacart.com"
    }
    summary: "The website captnemo.in, through a GitHub page titled \"Swiggy MCP Server,\" details the setup and integration of Swiggy\'s Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers for its Food, Instamart, and Dineout services[1]. This initiative allows developers to connect AI applications to Swiggy\'s commerce infrastructure.\n\nKey details found include:\n*   **Swiggy MCP Servers:** Instructions are provided for installing Swiggy MCP servers for Food, Instamart, and Dineout, with specific URLs for these services (e.g., `https://mcp.swiggy.com/food` and `https://mcp.swiggy.com/im`)[1].\n*   **Model Context Protocol (MCP):** MCP is described as an open-source standard that enables AI applications like Claude and ChatGPT to connect with external systems, data sources, and tools, functioning like a \"USB-C port for AI applications\"[2].\n*   **Swiggy Builders Club:** Swiggy has launched a \"Builders Club\" to give developers and enterprises access to its AI commerce stack, which includes APIs, MCP servers, and transactional capabilities across Swiggy Food, Instamart, and Dineout[3][4]. This club aims to facilitate the creation of AI agents, copilots, and integrations that can perform actions such as ordering food, shopping for groceries, or booking dining experiences[3][4].\n*   **Integration and Usage:** The GitHub page on captnemo.in lists supported OAuth Redirect URIs for MCP authentication, including those for `claude.ai`, `chatgpt.com`, and `vscode.dev`[1]. It also provides important notes on current limitations, such as disallowing third-party app development during security reviews, and cautions against opening the Swiggy app simultaneously with MCP integrations to avoid session conflicts[1].\n*   **Broader Context:** The MCP concept extends beyond Swiggy, with other platforms like Instacart also utilizing MCP servers to enable AI agents to interact with their services[5].\n\nSources:\n[1] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFpu3KRXtiXxd3DGiM_Suy-HNbjt9b6BQtgLXt1V977EyH3YEvqJxWE2M8sBCHifT82ySNmCnXuPq36zt9aV3wGPnxtNabiCFKMK6FHpmK_4PXpOi8B8lil9udMUEc0PSjDhi4Vc-oG1eNjzgo-DoI=)\n[2] [modelcontextprotocol.io](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFQ71QhicT4JJeMOcw_QmmMqu0LL5WJessRBmblN8dDqTqUt2Fl6-hzly1z4GD54YftFSg7Y4kxO35v8anakGPbcU6GEGROVeSWTA3GF4ctEgwTlBQSe3svTUkV8fQ17aCJGaS5XdSnF5Zo24hyceS_ETRM1SM=)\n[3] [aboutamazon.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGqY2ucLxju6I3tfEwKuxmDvnzcn_adf2EcSwYGjwB2jaXwYJL5IqbMYLDOlXoWhu8CjsItNQCQ8DlioMs_y4LASiaVSBO0JQPHSMyDbvAieMYSYm9kLKYzN1jQ15UHjb1vEExxssxoalvjKqlAfZTD6AzDgaCy8tibPzPIPwpoWG1XUH3AW784IBM4eb_xAnhrNnfze4SE5KhgvhUbWS6mR43uEUYXot7i9-NBmJOT9XCnZLwjrY2qJCOo9-cqcMwTaxFAWQ==)\n[4] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGKqTZg_TeFpGQnoYvjVLsiHWh6jXjNF8UvS8Dn9RTd_whzSdOkYQLuQ84bRcFMd_41G9nlu-Utcd9wf7Z1jzjFc-ImKsvNoPexHAocrY6wiDZeVBQn_w9Y2YRl)\n[5] [instacart.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHQ6wpqyHsVdHbWMRMx6PLrY963dAECBKWRmBVn05SM6OydTRNKmxBguT0EZxqSocFbgOHIOVFn72iwNTrv-K-2Lo9xzsDF7p2C-73kky4RWBX7viD5JhrK52fWBEvOrIW4MyDFDGBfZmoM3owx-F76g4wIgbpjeObQngKYyLGUDyo=)"
