    web_documents {
      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEtZ9msQkVeyva1TKIMFeLOeosLKdbpy8PLAYrN5DHBO74wU20igU8kK0NGSqoXtS7Kti7YfOKRRSS2-vPgFT21peZ1uiWmdD-Kmt-1WmOYfqNQFEcMtNmQOooT3KV0wbArFyZ1TJA9jNkHruiH-YuVGknTmuxz8HBsJD9sww7SxIr-Qw=="
      title: "google.com"
    }
    summary: "A search on `site:captnemo.in` for \"swiggy\" OR \"mcp\" OR \"Protocol\" OR \"manifest\" OR \"instamart\" reveals information primarily related to Swiggy\'s \"MCP\" (MyCommerce Protocol) and its associated services, including Instamart.\n\nKey findings include:\n*   **Swiggy MCP Server on GitHub:** There is a GitHub repository for \"Swiggy MCP Server\" that includes references to a manifest and URLs for Instamart (`https://mcp.swiggy.com/im`), Food (`https://mcp.swiggy.com/food`), and Dineout (`https://mcp.swiggy.com/dineout`). This server appears to be part of Swiggy\'s developer ecosystem. The manifest allows for adding \"mcpServers\" to integrate with Swiggy\'s services.[1]\n*   **Swiggy Builders Club:** Swiggy announced the launch of \"Swiggy Builders Club,\" a program designed for developers and enterprises to build AI-native commerce experiences on its platforms.[2] This initiative leverages Swiggy\'s \"MCP servers\" and provides access to APIs and transactional capabilities across Swiggy Food, Instamart, and Dineout.[2] The Builders Club aims to define how developers engage with Swiggy\'s infrastructure, which is built on AWS and powered by Amazon Bedrock and AgentCore.[2]\n*   **MCP and AI Commerce:** Swiggy\'s CTO, Madhusudhan Rao, stated that with MCP, Swiggy opened its commerce infrastructure to AI systems, and Builders Club is the next step in extending this access to developers.[2] This indicates a move towards becoming an \"ecosystem orchestrator\" for AI-native commerce innovation.[2]\n*   **Instamart and other Swiggy Services:** Instamart is highlighted as Swiggy\'s quick commerce platform, operating in over 124 cities and delivering groceries and essentials in minutes.[2][3] Swiggy also offers food delivery through \"Swiggy Food\" and dining out experiences via \"Dineout.\"[2][4][5] These services are integrated within the MCP ecosystem.[1][2]\n*   **Limitations and Usage:** For third-party app development, there are current limitations due to security reviews and compliance.[1] Users are advised not to open the official Swiggy app simultaneously with MCP integrations to avoid session conflicts.[1] Caution is also advised for Cash on Delivery (COD) orders placed through MCP integrations, as they cannot be canceled.[1]\n\nSources:\n[1] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHBbqJBDgiT__6te_C87O_7_3l-NkDkZBreEyNUWg7xlNyB1yknymB2FPuQo755O6y6y3Rv92-qg4gioFz3iYGkzhkhuQWnl-s6Rj8l_PLh0YJNBbw-hbHKWHh0laDvlK8uBBtSCIHtTp7qp1tN-wU=)\n[2] [aboutamazon.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFdHQSyTSGM0iq-fXEFhssHAiO-JXLS2NupLAdrJzsnlaAMkjqNzqg2tp9typr4jPXU3U5YXktUlLjzTnEJJN-QRGcAcd1EBudx5jkO51oWhKp4tYBSLgxx1prgVc92nkX7fo8yrKeANVU3PT-1VHbvUl9KbojKSSO0PRYXRT7viSetxXcSv_AG34RyFjAZvqRqxIh7E0f5Syd9pFO-jfH3peC88AcAGeCnyH8bj3n2SJ34_ICmu2OqyBLZe0xMx7mAUEkLtQ==)\n[3] [google.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEL_ENdwUkDo6qL4wLZoTe0eFBsJAPPlREWMuyxx91N1ZEbn5w68IFVI4-ZdigXa3X38feaHDUMFgjO24h7dLlxGKUcXonsjyTTNRi7b-Vr863Z7AIU9yhT8YFePh9Cp18ooOSfvKU7tYAQC5E3fQPY_AkqDUnpzcn-5Q==)\n[4] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHrRriJ0tLXTvdVVRU5XskFxWeTitbSshdemugloa8mQ_hEHI8y6JBUrzvepFuy-_ykn4G1EBSiV7b-Zyxdj_PrOdNM8EwwrVLu8MzxL2V2nrih)\n[5] [google.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEtZ9msQkVeyva1TKIMFeLOeosLKdbpy8PLAYrN5DHBO74wU20igU8kK0NGSqoXtS7Kti7YfOKRRSS2-vPgFT21peZ1uiWmdD-Kmt-1WmOYfqNQFEcMtNmQOooT3KV0wbArFyZ1TJA9jNkHruiH-YuVGknTmuxz8HBsJD9sww7SxIr-Qw==)"
