    summary: "Swiggy\'s MCP (Model Context Protocol) servers enable AI agents and chatbots to integrate with Swiggy\'s services, including food delivery, grocery ordering through Instamart, and restaurant reservations via Dineout.[1][2][3] This protocol allows AI systems to perform complex tasks by interacting with Swiggy\'s platform through intent-based commands, bypassing traditional app interfaces.[1][2]\n\nSwiggy launched its MCP integrations in January 2026, with Instamart becoming the first quick-commerce platform globally to adopt MCP.[1][2][3] This allows users to browse and purchase from over 40,000 SKUs using natural language prompts.[2][3] The MCP framework is open-source and facilitates secure interaction between AI systems and external applications.[1][2]\n\nThe Swiggy Builders Club program, which launched in April 2026, further extends this by providing developers, startups, and enterprises access to Swiggy\'s MCP servers and API tools to build AI-native commerce experiences.[4][5] These integrations support building AI assistants, copilots, and automations that can order food, groceries, or book tables on behalf of users.[4]\n\nThere is no direct information found linking \"captnemo,\" \"captnemo.in,\" or a blog by this entity to Swiggy\'s MCP server in the search results.\n\nSources:\n[1] [indiatimes.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGow2czB0FTw3vs7jhskNK6VuZVGOlHbo7OZAXLdC3myhG8B4pHtCzeUpgMZjBYVjn0w-p6hG9NKdJPk6b9p-44BPDXBzJNsuDwl-9L4oQFfnuSusD4hh0xKUb0VYxx9zOPfpbaSlm0i-_LrV_4PeOOeV9cBKByT_9EiMBrI7ETfVtFe69NeShrBHh1z70ZiDIsvKRWdRJV3hXkk-VxTrs_Es1wMmiSUfOsDBfPH4qdQjNtxdNwAM3Qv1nJOgf1vGzlm_0p)\n[2] [fortuneindia.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGEtZJDfSFVoj_9yzCq0UFz5fYh-AK_LiBbZeK1JQ8IRhtEcnTqX4yjnSdfk93Si7BBi8vgHRp6ySX8x6B6fQ7-3NhmZoMXfb1lNmlZ3g_nNJluFTmMPAlnUNqEp_txS5H01ooo9m3DO_4QQb4-zOOnszon65vqmdmH3aHOzcPEOxo85LMx-Wshjdt7QKr7xSuBkLotbZBlm5vRfTXhK_OyqqNLyQ5waK-ZdRiJi