    web_documents {
      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHpxiugC49FuMUwK2Q19HnI3Z2dLUVIGCJ8AKD-Z0qkcAev9RPUjxUHAFYUdvyTrDZeo4AAfvsuofT6AaDW6CHn96u7c-2JGkLe8U0pbpYhzePSHljFqDiTAc4qbG8KNh4Qk-qs-xgoXA=="
      title: "apify.com"
    }
    summary: "Swiggy MCP (Model Context Protocol) Servers allow AI agents to interact with Swiggy\'s commerce platform, encompassing Food, Instamart, and Dineout services. These servers act as an open standard for various AI tools and frameworks.[1][2]\n\nHere\'s how to get started with or set up Swiggy MCP Servers:\n\n**Understanding Swiggy MCP**\n*   **Purpose:** Swiggy MCP exposes three distinct services: Food (for restaurant discovery, menus, and ordering), Instamart (for quick-commerce grocery), and Dineout (for table reservations).[1][2][3][4]\n*   **Target Audience:** It\'s designed for agent developers utilizing AI SDKs (like OpenAI Agents SDK, Anthropic SDK, LangGraph, Vercel AI SDK), agent platforms, and users of AI clients such as Claude Desktop, ChatGPT, Cursor, and VS Code.[1][5][6]\n*   **Authentication:** The system uses standard OAuth 2.1 with PKCE for authentication.[2][3] A single token is issued for all three servers, which simplifies the initial connection but necessitates careful handling of OAuth expiry and retry logic.[2]\n\n**Setup and Getting Started Instructions**\n\nSeveral methods exist for setting up and integrating with Swiggy MCP Servers:\n\n1.  **Manual Setup:**\n    *   You can configure the MCP servers by editing a local `mcp.json` file and then reloading your client. This method does not require installing a local server.[7]\n\n2.  **LobeHub Integration:**\n    *   For LobeHub Desktop app users, navigate to \"Settings\" > \"Skill Settings\" > \"Custom Skills.\"\n    *   Select \"Quick Import JSON Configuration\" and paste the provided server configuration to install.[7]\n\n3.  **AI Client Integration (e.g., Claude Desktop, Cursor, VS Code):**\n    *   Many AI clients offer direct integration. For example, in Claude Desktop, you would go to \"Settings\" > \"Connectors\" > \"Add custom connector\" and then add the specific URLs for Swiggy Food (`https://mcp.swiggy.com/food`), Instamart (`https://mcp.swiggy.com/im`), and Dineout (`https://mcp.swiggy.com/dineout`).[3] Similar \"Install MCP Server\" options are available for Cursor and VS Code.[3]\n\n4.  **Developer Quickstart:**\n    *   This path involves integrating Swiggy MCP tools into your agent code against a staging endpoint.[5]\n    *   Key steps include understanding the MCP tool call loop, requesting access (as production access is whitelist-only), choosing an MCP-compatible framework (e.g., OpenAI Agents SDK, LangChain), and then making your first tool call.[5]\n\n5.  **Apify Configuration:**\n    *   A pre-configured setup is available for the Swiggy Restaurant Scraper Actor on an Apify MCP server, which can be connected to using various MCP clients.[8]\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n*   **Geographical Limitation:** Swiggy MCP currently serves an India-only user base.[1]\n*   **Access:** Production access is granted via an invite-based whitelist onboarding process.[1][5]\n*   **Third-Party Development:** Third-party app development is temporarily restricted due to ongoing security reviews.[3]\n*   **Simultaneous Use:** Avoid using the Swiggy app simultaneously with MCP integrations to prevent potential session conflicts or order processing issues.[3]\n*   **COD Orders:** Be cautious with Cash on Delivery (COD) orders placed through MCP, as they cannot be canceled; always review your cart before confirming.[3]\n\nSources:\n[1] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFZeqiX0zOLim8jQhGIv9pF0qZAczZTor2-2q1h-kjj7EL-Ws52886HHjmtK9DNYK_S4O6v4O112GQstwdge_L-p6z9Iv6s5mvpIaLwmV98GMgQ3LwL1asPTukJEDgeauVES90s8BRjpGIXpfoe7ZDPsWXVXh9iQ5lc)\n[2] [medium.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGj7rNpncRNavE3roF8gcRKoXWTzzH_29cecLUpr4SYquQPBYWVHhqU5HVG0RHKsq608vRsPcopDi-H3775hCIZqmsLjk6ylFoKEeUuIX1jztg15uR9v_ZRujkUiyXFgPvboCBpTwQPntsvBPPDrJtiem3xnoeKucaaPDs_WxQA1jSRxBhMGbSp6HeT7dVzSdhiOOtlFCp2j0rcsiVv2t7Gwrz7i4ysKTJu54AK6KHTsf_coRt7-d5NwWMl-PABJmULDgoTEDW_)\n[3] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGw89dKdWA9Eho2GKvG3ci7K0zu9NOcSOtLTD_sCMqUXqW2aY0Os6rQshHOmUZhiabL5ku25REU2-W_DguAGJkiaQ2rXjgLj-3_1-dvQyAfR56OlW4mOAYANwaZMZCv3OTDiJnhM4beMkPmuiblDcY=)\n[4] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFGC96B6WXjK87m4j0hDMYeCLrkMveGN1KxW6Jm5jOdkLTTRpFuoD0hzxyvvqlYtRgtEBKAxORr403Pi0S2xoF3Js-fJnYzfVDeoTVt8EuGZVIPeRxK0d6lpQ5_mc0nWhTh961acMSrBr_V)\n[5] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFNELXfWZHl8V8kPRqRM5HdOofO3OPUvUQ-N6ObKsFH40ZowwFHtVGEP35IgZwR4_T_9VnUqxvPAi50SQUyTEjqv9ityLS_cUXR10SDyuZi_q3N3M6DmGePDyAJGx8hl68bVA-nY8chCw0n7F6iGpEv)\n[6] [swiggy.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEltSd2JWosq0q_WRlz3QbpgCpe3zobdfzfVKw3e8hjJIqCo8yDeWUGdhpE-C0g8HWPrI-sNUOV-KeWQ1dozHJ11zrmft5uZJIwFPDyt6Aj8P_Orv8OGDo2trJA0NXDoBs=)\n[7] [lobehub.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHf3lUsQeSvJlhfocigJIwBZboQ2QEQntBGvR2kNY5Q593PfLEkuXJuuaDtDBfcuJk-G7NofEuyhSRiSAb08TwZHslqT8MFyAxJsTnAwFG_XebuqieJ_Gyv0h0vjghZ2TCJSWFkfwG9S9XHju9_U938PObpYvSiQQ5hYJHKJdeA8sqfV7PseOXaew==)\n[8] [apify.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHpxiugC49FuMUwK2Q19HnI3Z2dLUVIGCJ8AKD-Z0qkcAev9RPUjxUHAFYUdvyTrDZeo4AAfvsuofT6AaDW6CHn96u7c-2JGkLe8U0pbpYhzePSHljFqDiTAc4qbG8KNh4Qk-qs-xgoXA==)"
