      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEUWRRmjF94dFX2Jd6Qg7FeOs6kh4Ru2dItDvTv8ka_FY4i0I4HrYnknJdssypQyQH9nE7z6k_o1KdR1fWLG4m5LpTzBwOPNAb_sfuUoxCSWQft1I-GO66Fp6aJFni0AlI2pZcno3kbv4J4gS00P3hrm0mSPfGnLw=="
      title: "github.com"
    }
    summary: "The `@swiggy/mcp-server` refers to Swiggy\'s implementation of a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server, designed to enable AI assistants to directly interact with Swiggy\'s various services. This includes food delivery, Instamart, and Dineout[1][2].\n\nKey details about the Swiggy MCP Server and the Model Context Protocol:\n*   **Purpose** The Swiggy MCP Server acts as a backend integration layer, allowing AI tools like ChatGPT and Gemini to access Swiggy\'s services through conversational commands[2]. Users can, for example, ask an AI assistant to \"order dinner from Swiggy,\" and the MCP server facilitates this by converting natural language requests into structured actions[2].\n*   **Functionality** The server handles user authentication, verifies the actions an AI is permitted to perform, and maintains the context of interactions, such as past orders and preferences[2]. It then securely communicates with Swiggy\'s internal APIs to execute tasks like fetching user\'s usual orders, adding items to a cart, or placing orders[2].\n*   **Technology** The Swiggy MCP Server utilizes Playwright-backed browser sessions for controlled browser-session operations[3]. It does not require external data files for its operations[1].\n*   **Model Context Protocol (MCP)** MCP is a broader framework that dictates how AI models can request information or perform actions on external systems in a controlled and authorized manner[2]. It acts as a middleware, ensuring safety, consistency, and proper authorization between AI assistants and application services[2].\n*   **Related Implementations** Beyond Swiggy, the MCP framework is also used in other contexts, such as the \"Labamu MCP Server\" for managing business APIs related to material inventory and vendor management, and the \"BC MCP Server\" for integrating AI agents with Microsoft Dynamics 365 Business Central ERP modules[1][4].\n*   **Development** There is an associated GitHub repository, `Swiggy/swiggy-mcp-server-manifest`, which suggests active development and management of the server\'s manifests or deployment configurations[5].\n\nSources:\n[1] [lobehub.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF7M68Cs2CL67YMkNTbTztGB0S2gNPX2Tswznok5DOJvjywb1YocWgzltD4Z9Qud23mB0B5HgXW3N9EaInPLUYIlwc3KWiJNN2FhfDlv5GiW8cwdNKVyicrmVF38-s8c6OUo8j8IK0=)\n[2] [geeksforgeeks.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEyigWlCX3FNqCZMU35W_2GNCbLDjvlCUvTT8xNHq9dPfve6BWyL5VqtGdgPy4WTvzkfFi6UaQPHWSBStS5Kut5j2RhoJ8v0gtmactMkB6ssFhmYuOpBobHyikPEW0oxdbsZxxXCtjzWYWB4fmavQ==)\n[3] [arpitkhandelwal.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGVmjUNZ1vL4UNEU7fAepAaU1mmvaE1XrXH8ZKL61d-3rDEzE5akSVrMgWmBhmgZBgqR-eTu-tyb5Vxlg4iwHTQilH-M0HCFS6KihLekOUliQZOeIjOrrBUfJyT)\n[4] [lobehub.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHdECOHmSx86ghl6KbEtVuWMCLtc-IZjqVnJrj9SVHSqQiIOcUGbezdFo6F82T4dvlpTM6AprJv33SjXOhDxLDVkiJUjugeVXKwmoOmpbvaIZesGt3OoVfhVB1pYtttqAzHoF_vJ-3tuKqXrX4=)\n[5] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEUWRRmjF94dFX2Jd6Qg7FeOs6kh4Ru2dItDvTv8ka_FY4i0I4HrYnknJdssypQyQH9nE7z6k_o1KdR1fWLG4m5LpTzBwOPNAb_sfuUoxCSWQft1I-GO66Fp6aJFni0AlI2pZcno3kbv4J4gS00P3hrm0mSPfGnLw==)"
